                    </div>
                    <span>What the Buddha Taught was written in 1959. It is a little dry, but goes right to the core of Buddhism.
<br />It is continually being printed in new editions.  I first came across this book in a religion course in college.  It is written like a college text, and is written to educate, not inspire.  
<br /></span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Joy and peace never had before!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
